Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase and all existing features. Let me look at one more thing to finalize my proposal:Based on my thorough analysis of the entire codebase, I can see:

- **Speaking tab**: 15 card types (speak, shadow, opinion, story, follow-up, idiom, question, explain, role-play, tongue twister, rapid fire, sentence stress, register switch, debate, scene description)
- **Listening tab**: 7 card types (dictation, listen-respond, listen-paraphrase, minimal pairs, listening comp, spot-error, predict-next)
- **Dictation**: word-for-word transcription of single sentences (typing)
