The clear gap: **No dictogloss-style exercise** — a proven SLA technique where learners listen to a multi-sentence passage at normal speed, then reconstruct the content from memory by speaking. This is fundamentally different from dictation (word-for-word typing), shadowing (immediate repetition), and summarization (condensing). Dictogloss forces deep meaning processing and grammatically accurate production from memory.

